Why did you choose your field?
In junior high school I started collecting church bulletins and printed copies of the ministers’ sermons. Why? What we did on Sunday mornings seemed urgent and I wanted to know more.

If you feel called to serve the world through Christian ministry or service—to both lean into your faith and question your assumptions; to both connect with a vibrant community and find your unique place in it; to both channel your conviction and broaden your impact—follow that calling to Austin Presbyterian Theological Seminary.
There’s an accessible intimacy at Austin Seminary that you don’t get at other places.
Admissions Associate and Director of Financial Aid

The Admissions Office is here to guide you through the process of discerning if this is the right place to continue your journey. We invite you to campus, especially to one of our Discovery Weekends, where you can get a taste for what to expect as an Austin Seminary student.

The city itself I was drawn to: the climate, the surroundings. The campus was gorgeous. Being right in the middle of downtown was just vibrant and fun.

Our home in the heart of Austin brings culture, creativity, and diversity to our doorstep, allowing you to engage in service and learning beyond the bounds of the Seminary campus. Oh. And did we mention queso?
Austin Seminary is located in the heart of one of the greatest cities on the planet. But don’t just take our word for it:

Students at Austin Seminary find plenty to do in this active, creative city—and with around 300 days of sunshine, much of it’s done outdoors. The city that launched Twitter (SWSX, 2011) and inspired the creation of Whole Foods, Tito's, and Dell Computers offers University of Texas football, Formula One racing, Barton Spring Pool, and enough marathons and music festivals to tie up traffic from here to eternity. On the quirky side, we have 1.5 million Mexican free-tailed bats living under a bridge downtown and a 50 -year tradition of celebrating Eeyore’s birthday. You won’t get hungry here either with 2000 food trucks, loads of mouth-watering barbecue, and, sigh, breakfast tacos!
